issue.title: OpenCV version issue?
issue.body:
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ".\Gesture.py", line 45, in <module>
    contours, hierarchy = cv2.findContours(thresh, cv2.RETR_TREE, cv2.CHAIN_APPROX_SIMPLE)
ValueError: too many values to unpack (expected 2)

Looks like it requires a specific version of OpenCV. Would you please post your requirements.txt file?

Thanks

comment.body:
Not sure how it worked in your side but it turned out to be a bug in my side. Changing the line to blow has resolved the issue (assign the return to 3 variables rather than 2):
_, contours, hierarchy = cv2.findContours(thresh, cv2.RETR_TREE, cv2.CHAIN_APPROX_SIMPLE)

Regards
